11#ifndef MEDIA_BASE_H264_PROFILE_LEVEL_ID_H_
12#define MEDIA_BASE_H264_PROFILE_LEVEL_ID_H_
13
14#include <string>
15
16#include "api/video_codecs/h264_profile_level_id.h"
17
18// TODO(crbug.com/1187565): Remove this file once downstream projects stop
19// depend on it.
20
21namespace webrtc {
22namespace H264 {
23
24typedef H264Profile Profile;
25typedef H264Level Level;
26typedef H264ProfileLevelId ProfileLevelId;
27
28constexpr H264Profile kProfileConstrainedBaseline =
29 H264Profile::kProfileConstrainedBaseline;
30constexpr H264Profile kProfileBaseline = H264Profile::kProfileBaseline;
31constexpr H264Profile kProfileMain = H264Profile::kProfileMain;
32constexpr H264Profile kProfileConstrainedHigh =
33 H264Profile::kProfileConstrainedHigh;
34constexpr H264Profile kProfileHigh = H264Profile::kProfileHigh;
35
36constexpr H264Level kLevel1_b = H264Level::kLevel1_b;
37constexpr H264Level kLevel1 = H264Level::kLevel1;
38constexpr H264Level kLevel1_1 = H264Level::kLevel1_1;
39constexpr H264Level kLevel1_2 = H264Level::kLevel1_2;
40constexpr H264Level kLevel1_3 = H264Level::kLevel1_3;
41constexpr H264Level kLevel2 = H264Level::kLevel2;
42constexpr H264Level kLevel2_1 = H264Level::kLevel2_1;
43constexpr H264Level kLevel2_2 = H264Level::kLevel2_2;
44constexpr H264Level kLevel3 = H264Level::kLevel3;
45constexpr H264Level kLevel3_1 = H264Level::kLevel3_1;
46constexpr H264Level kLevel3_2 = H264Level::kLevel3_2;
47constexpr H264Level kLevel4 = H264Level::kLevel4;
48constexpr H264Level kLevel4_1 = H264Level::kLevel4_1;
49constexpr H264Level kLevel4_2 = H264Level::kLevel4_2;
50constexpr H264Level kLevel5 = H264Level::kLevel5;
51constexpr H264Level kLevel5_1 = H264Level::kLevel5_1;
52constexpr H264Level kLevel5_2 = H264Level::kLevel5_2;
53
54// Parse profile level id that is represented as a string of 3 hex bytes.
55// Nothing will be returned if the string is not a recognized H264
56// profile level id.
57absl::optional<ProfileLevelId> ParseProfileLevelId(const char* str);
58
59// Parse profile level id that is represented as a string of 3 hex bytes
60// contained in an SDP key-value map. A default profile level id will be
61// returned if the profile-level-id key is missing. Nothing will be returned if
62// the key is present but the string is invalid.
63RTC_EXPORT absl::optional<ProfileLevelId> ParseSdpProfileLevelId(
64 const SdpVideoFormat::Parameters& params);
65
66// Given that a decoder supports up to a given frame size (in pixels) at up to a
67// given number of frames per second, return the highest H.264 level where it
68// can guarantee that it will be able to support all valid encoded streams that
69// are within that level.
70RTC_EXPORT absl::optional<Level> SupportedLevel(int max_frame_pixel_count,
71 float max_fps);
72
73// Returns canonical string representation as three hex bytes of the profile
74// level id, or returns nothing for invalid profile level ids.
75RTC_EXPORT absl::optional<std::string> ProfileLevelIdToString(
76 const ProfileLevelId& profile_level_id);
77
78// Returns true if the parameters have the same H264 profile, i.e. the same
79// H264::Profile (Baseline, High, etc).
80RTC_EXPORT bool IsSameH264Profile(const SdpVideoFormat::Parameters& params1,
81 const SdpVideoFormat::Parameters& params2);
82
83} // namespace H264
84} // namespace webrtc
